what we have, it=E2=80=99s what we do. The separate and coequal branches of=
 government are not inert constitutional provisions. They=E2=80=99re about =
exercising power. And I think that wins beget wins, and losses beget losses=
=2E People are desperate and terrified.=
 And I understand that point of view.=20=
But we have to not presume we are powerless. Like it or not, the filibuster=
 is still in place. So if Donald Trump doesn=E2=80=99t like one of these la=
ws, he can=E2=80=99t waive it by executive order; he=E2=80=99s got to come =
back to us. If
he wants a federal spending bill, he=E2=80=99s gotta come back to us. If he=
 wants to waive any of the provisions of any statute, he has to come back t=
o us. And look, I think the courts are going to back him when it=E2=80=99s =
close, but we have to remember, some of the things that he=E2=80=99s doing =
are not close. I don=E2=80=99t think he=E2=80=99s going to get rid of birth=
right citizenship because the constitutional language is absolutely plain.

=C2=A0

All I would say is that if we=E2=80=99re going to win this, everybody has t=
o live somewhere in between =E2=80=9Cwe are cooked=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cwe=
 are going to be just fine.=E2=80=9D But we have to be vigilant. We have to=
 work together. We have to kick ass. And as my old friend, the former Speak=
er of the Hawaii House of Representatives Calvin Say, used to say: Be like =
the bamboo=E2=80=94bend, but don=E2=80=99t break.

